<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Indonesia to Enhance Economic Collaboration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Indonesia have
agreed to enhance trade and economic collaboration to the benefit
of the two countries, visiting President of Indonesia Abdurrahman
Wahid and Chief Executive of Pakistan General Pervez Musharraf
stated here Friday in a joint press conference.
</P>
<P>
President Wahid said his visit here will strengthen relations
between Pakistan and Indonesia and both countries shall enhance
their cooperation in trade and technology. He suggested that
Pakistan can specially help Indonesia in the field of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
General Pervez Musharraf said both countries feel they have
certain important role to play in the region and in Asia as they
are the third and fourth largest Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
He said they discussed the scope of bilateral relations and
agreed that bilateral economic relations can be enhanced to new
levels.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian President arrived here Friday afternoon for a
two-day official visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
