<HEADLINE> OAU Chief to Attend Ethiopian-Eritrean Ceasefire Signing Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General Salim Ahmed
Salim of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) will attend the
ceremony marking the signing of the agreement between Ethiopia and
Eritrea on cessation of hostilities.
</P>
<P>
Salim left here Friday for Algiers, the capital of Algeria,
where the ceremony is to be held, an OAU press release said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrean, which have been at war for border
disputes since May 1998, are due to sign the OAU-prepared
Cessation of Hostilities Agreement on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The two belligerent countries agreed to sign the peace deal to
end their two-year-old border war after the OAU made sustained
mediation.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of soldiers of the two countries were
reportedly killed and wounded while hundreds of thousands of
people became war refugees during the bloody border conflict.
</P>
</TEXT>
