<HEADLINE> Van Almsick Qualifies for Her Third Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- German swimmer Franziska van
Almsick on Friday qualified for this summer's Sydney Olympic Games,
her third straight Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old won the 200 meters butterfly with a time of two
minutes 10.58 seconds in the national trials here.
</P>
<P>
She was 200 meters freestyle silver medallist in both Barcelona
and Atlanta Olympic Games. 
</P>
