<HEADLINE> IOC to Begin Accrediting East Timorese Athletes for Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- An International Olympic Committee
(IOC) delegation will meet with East Timorese leaders and United
Nations officials on June 17-18 to initiate the process of
accrediting local athletes to participate in the Sydney Olympic
games.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by IOC Vice President Kevan Gosper, will
also determine how the IOC can help East Timor develop a national
Olympic committee (NOC), the IOC said in a press release today.
</P>
<P>
The IOC delegation will meet with the East Timorese sports
leaders to identify which athletes are qualified to compete in the
Olympic Games. The IOC will ensure these athletes, once identified,
are given opportunities to prepare for competition.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will also outline the proper procedures the East
Timorese must follow in order to develop an NOC in accordance with
the Olympic Charter.
</P>
<P>
In doing so, the delegation will explore opportunities to
normalize Olympic sports in East Timor with the full cooperation
of the relevant international sports federations. The IOC will
continue to monitor the process and provide assistance as
appropriate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
