<HEADLINE> France Beats Czech Republic 2-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- World champion France took a 2-1
win over defending runner-up Czech Republic on Friday in the Euro
2000 Group D match at the Jan Breydel Stadium in Bruges, Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Thierry Henry opened the scoring only seven minute into the
game for France but Czech Republic's Karel Poborsky equallied in
the 35th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Frenchmen jumped the lead again with Youri Djorkaeff's
winning goal in the 60th minute to secure their hope of
qualification for the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
France won all two matches for six points while Czech lost two
in the group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
