<HEADLINE> England Fans in Scuffles in Brussels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BRUSSELS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of English soccer fans
scuffled with Belgians of north African descent Friday evening
near the capital city's stock exchange, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
About 100 riot police descended on the area bordering Brussels
' famous Grand Place after some England fans began charging at
police, Reuters said.
</P>
<P>
Some of the fans threw beer, cans and plastic cups at passing
cars. Police closed the main street in front of the stock exchange
to traffic as fans swarmed onto the street,chanting "Rule
Britannia", after a nearby Irish-style bar was closed.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Friday, police arrested three England soccer fans
as supporters who had been drinking all afternoon fought with
police in the city's famous Grand'Place, the report added.
</P>
</TEXT>
