<HEADLINE> 10 Killed, 9 Injured in Road Accidents in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Ten people were killed and nine
others injured in Egypt on Saturday in two traffic accidents,
including a hit-and-run collision of a truck into a funeral
procession, the Interior Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver sped off after running into the funeral party
and killing three people in the town of Akhmim in southern Egypt,
said a statement issued by the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The driver then hit three cars before his vehicle overturned and
he was arrested, the country's Middle East News Agency quoted the
statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
Another seven people died and nine were injured when a truck
collided head-on with a bus on the road linking Cairo and the
eastern town of Suez. The truck driver was trying to overtake a car
when he smashed into the bus, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt due to reckless driving
and violations of regulations. The Interior Ministry has reported
that an average of 3,000 people are killed in road accidents each
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
