<HEADLINE> Ecuadorian Oil Exports Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Profits from Ecuadorian oil exports
in the first four months of this year grew 168.6 percent compared
to the same period of 1999, said Saturday the Ecuadorian Central
Bank (ECB).
</P>
<P>
ECB statistics show that the income from crude exports between
January and April amounted to 668.9 million U.S. dollars, against
249.03 million dollars in the same 1999 period.
</P>
<P>
January's exports revenue, 182.4 million dollars, was the
highest not only of the first four months of this year, but also
of the monthly value of the last two years.
</P>
<P>
Oil leads, with the increase of exports revenue, all the
products of this country sold abroad and surpasses by more than
100 percent banana exports, which are second in the list with 328.
5 million dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
Petroleos del Ecuador (PETROECUADOR), the state oil company,
informed that the oil exports increase is mainly due to the price
of the barrel of crude in the international market, now quoted at
26.3 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
