<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
Saturday warned that his government and the ruling Zimbabwe
African National Union- Patriotic Front (Zanu-pf) will intensify a
fight against corruption.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a campaign rally for the ruling party for the next
week's parliamentary elections in Harare, Mugabe said action
would be taken against all those found guilty.
</P>
<P>
