expose corruption at all levels, both in government, and in civic
society including city councils," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe also accused some white Zimbabweans of failing to
embrace his government's policy of reconciliation, conspiring and
aligning themselves with the opposition and other enemies of the
state.
</P>
<P>
He said by acquiring land the government was completing the
revolution to the end and ideals of bringing total control of land
and the economy to blacks.
</P>
<P>
He said the government supported war veterans on farm invasions
adding that nothing would happen to them.
</P>
<P>
"No blackman can be president in the United States to this
date," he said. "Racism will always be there in Britain and the
United States yet they continue to point their fingers at us."
</P>
<P>
"A racial future will never be acceptable in Zimbabwe, but
racial harmony will continue provided whites accept and agree to
live with and among the blacks," he said, adding "they will
always be free to follow their own culture and religion."
