<HEADLINE> Chinese All-Stars Edge NBA Ambassadors 83-80 in Super League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, China, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Basketball
Association (CBA) All-Stars edged NBA Ambassadors 83-80 here on
Saturday in the first leg of the fourth round of the Asian Super
League competition.
</P>
<P>
In the first two quarters, the Chinese posted big centers Yao
Ming and Wang Zhizhi but failed to beat the faster and more
skilled NBA All-Stars, trailing the Ambassadors 16-22 after the
first quarter and 34-39 after the second.
</P>
<P>
The third quarter saw the CBA All-Stars stage a rally by
revving up the attacks with Yao and Wang substituted and focusing
long-range shots from outside.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese rebuilt their confidence after hitting four three-
pointers and concluded the third quarter 66-59.
</P>
<P>
In the fourth quarter, NBA Ambassadors pressed harder with
aggressive coverage of the key Chinese players and forced the CBA
All-Stars into mistakes under the basket.
</P>
<P>
With 30 seconds to go, the two sides were tied 80-80. Liu
Yudong made a successful under-basket attack and then converted a
free throw to seal the victory.
</P>
<P>
The CBA All-Stars remain unbeaten in seven games at the six-
team tournament. The other All-Stars teams are from Chinese Taipei,
South Korea, Hong Kong and Japan.
</P>
<P>
In other games on Saturday, Hong Kong All-stars lost to Chinese
Taipei All-Stars 98-94 at home while South Korean All-Stars routed
visiting Japanese All-Stars 112-97. 
</P>
