<HEADLINE> Turkish President Stresses Urgency of Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer
warned on Saturday the environmental problems have deteriorated to
threaten the future of humanity.
</P>
<P>
Sezer issued the warning in a message on the occasion of the
United Nations "Combat Against Desertification Day," which falls on
June 17 every year, reported the Anatolia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Sezer noted it is getting more imperative to maintain
sustainable development, tackle the environmental problems so as to
hand over a clean world to the forthcoming generations.
</P>
<P>
He urged all the countries to embrace and implement the
principle of sustainable development and prevent squandering of
resources.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey supports the international initiatives and programs
regarding the solution of environmental problems," he said,
referring to the Turkish parliament's adoption of the United
Nations Convention to Combat Desertification which Ankara signed in
1994 and ratified in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Sezer said priority should be given to activities aimed at
enhancing the environmental consciousness in the society.
</P>
<P>
"The sensitivity we show to environment will contribute to
significant solutions," he added.
</P>
<P>
Turkey promulgated a National Afforestation and Erosion Control
Mobilization Law in 1995 with the objective of increasing the
number of trees in the state forests and on land owned by juristic
persons and protecting environmental assets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
