<HEADLINE> "Spring Bud 2000" Project Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The "Spring Bud 2000" Program, a
national campaign to help female school dropouts in poor areas,
started today in the capital of northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Spring Bud Project has helped over 900,000 female students
continue their studies since it was launched in 1989.
</P>
<P>
An official with the China Children and Teenagers Fund said the
program has collected over 300 million yuan (about 36 million U.S.
dollars) in the past decade.
</P>
<P>
About ten million children who drop out of school need help
each year, sources say.
</P>
<P>
"Spring Bud 2000" will continue to help all girl drop-outs
return to school and complete their nine years of compulsory
education this year by collecting fund and organizing charity
concerts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
