<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Island Province to Build Large Fertilizer Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A large natural gas fertilizer
plant with an investment of three billion yuan (about 362 million
U.S. dollars) will be built in Dongfang city in China's
southernmost province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
The plant will produce 450,000 tons of synthetic ammonia and
800,000 tons of carbamide. The plant will be operational by
November 2003, said China National Offshore Oil Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The company will also invest another five billion yuan (about
602.4 million U.S. dollars) to develop a natural gas field.
</P>
</TEXT>
