<HEADLINE> Daily Air Quality Report for 42 Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Chengdu in southwest China
reported slight air pollution today, while very little air
pollution was recorded in Beijing, Tianjin, Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan,
Shenyang, Yantai, Wuhan, Changsha, Guangzhou, Chongqing, Guiyang,
Lanzhou and Urumqi.
</P>
<P>
According to the daily report issued today by the China
Environmental Monitoring Center, air conditions were fairly good
in Hohhot, Dalian, Changchun, Harbin, Shanghai, Nanjing, Suzhou,
Nantong, Hangzhou, Wenzhou, Hefei, Fuzhou, Nanchang, Qingdao,
Zhengzhou, Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Zhanjiang, Nanning, Kunming, Lhasa,
Xi'an, Xining and Yinchuan.
</P>
<P>
All the 42 aforementioned cities but six listed particulates
less than 10 microns in size as their major pollutants.
</P>
<P>
Of the other four cities, Xiamen, Jinan, Shantou and Haikou
reported excellent air conditions, and Chongqing and Kunming
reported sulfur dioxide as their major air pollutant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
