<HEADLINE> Nepali Ministries to Go on Web </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Nepali government ministries
will soon go cyber with each of the ministries getting its own
websites on the Internet, a report said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Science and Technology Surendra Chaudhary told the
parliament Friday that all the ministries will have their own
websites that would describe detailed activities of these
ministries,including their policies and future strategies, said
The Kathmandu Post.
</P>
<P>
"The government is aggressively moving toward developing the
information technology sector despite the fact that the sector has
not been allocated adequate budget," said Chaudhary.
</P>
<P>
The government is planning to operate its own VSAT (vertical
satellite) that will be stationed at the Ministry of Science and
Technology to connect all the ministries on the Internet and is
planning to assist all the universities in the nation to get their
own VSATs, according to Chaudhary.
</P>
<P>
At present only a couple of government departments like the
Department of Tax and the Value Added Tax Department have their
own websites. 
</P>
