<HEADLINE> China Wins First Match in Final Qualifying Tourney for Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Olympics silver medallists
China opened their campaign in victorious note after beating
Canada 3-0 on Saturday in the women's volleyball final qualifying
round for the Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
China, which also beat the same opponent in their last
encounter five years ago, won 25-18, 25-13 and 25-13.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese failed to qualify for Sydney at the World Cup in
November after finishing fifth and had to go through this final
tournament in order to book a ticket to Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The country which finishes top will take the first ticket for
Sydney. Then the top Asian country will qualify as Asian
qualifiers, and the best two teams among the remaining six
countries will get the last two places for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"We couldn't do well at the World Cup, because we missed two
main players due to injuries and it affected us very much," said
Chinese head coach Hu Jin after the 66-minute match.
</P>
<P>
"Today, He Qi and Li Shan did very well alongside Sun Yue, and
Wu Dan also played. I think our team is stronger than before,"
added Hu.
</P>
<P>
In other actions on Saturday, South Korea beat Croatia 25-16,
25-18, 25-20 while Italy came back from two sets down to beat the
Netherlands 22-25, 19-25, 25-19, 25-23 and 15-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
