<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- French dairy food, water and biscuit company Danone
said on Friday that it had bought Turkish mineral water company
Flora, which would be run by its Danone Sa unit jointly owned with
the Turkish conglomerate Sabanci.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's mineral water market was estimated at 1.2 billion
litres last year.
</P>
<P>
Danone is the world's second largest company in bottle water.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Canada's top fund management company, Caisse De Depot,
is planning to come to Turkey both for short- and long-term
investments.
</P>
<P>
Caisse De Depot, which handles 160 billion U.S. dollars in
investor's funds, invested 75 million dollars in Turkey last year -
- a large portion of which in Treasury bills -- and earned profits
as high as 50 percent on the investments in U.S. dollar terms.
</P>
<P>
The company is assessing investment possibilities in several
Turkish sectors, including privatization and banking, for five-year
or longer periods.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Four Turkish families, Karamehmet, Sabanci, Koc and
Sahenk, were listed among the richest 315 people and families of
the world in 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to U.S. business magazine Forbes, Mehmet Karamehmet
and his family, with a wealth of 8 billion dollars earned in the
finance and telecommunications, ranked the 45th in the world
richest.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's second richest, Sakip Sabanci and his family, had a
wealth of 5.7 billion dollars and was ranked 75th on the list.
</P>
<P>
Rahmi Koc and his family with a wealth of 4.4 billion, and Ayhan
Sahenk and his family with 3.6 billion were also listed among the
richest in the world.
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The United Arab Emirates foreign trade (export,
import and re-export) through the northeast emirate of Fujairah
stood at 4.21 billion dirhams (1.15 billion dollars) last year,
according to an official report.
</P>
<P>
Import stood at 2.75 billion dirhams (751.3 million dollars),
accounting for 65.3 percent of the total foreign trade, while
exports were put at 312.2 million dirhams (85.3 million dollars)
and re-export 1.15 billion dirhams (314.2 million dollars), the
report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
