<HEADLINE> 15 Filipinos Injured in Road Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 persons were hurt
Friday afternoon when a minibus lost its brakes and rammed a car
before plowing into a parked passenger jeepney in Carcar town of
Negros Oriental Province in the central Philippines.
</P>
<P>
A report of the Philippine News Agency said Saturday that the
driver of the minibus quickly surrendered to the Carcar police
station after his vehicle rammed the car driven by a police
officer.
</P>
<P>
Because of the impact, the car was thrown a few meters away and
it crashed into a house, injuring both the police officer and his
passenger. The report said the police officer suffered a puncture
wound in his neck when he was impaled on a guava tree.
</P>
<P>
After hitting the car, the minibus careered into a passenger
jeepney. The impact caused the passenger jeepney to turn sideways
and injured all its 13 passengers, including a one-year-old boy
and a 91-year-old man, said the report. 
</P>
