disease was brought under control.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a peasant farmer in the Sesheke district as
saying that he had lost about eight animals since the disease
broke out.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian government should consider establishing an animal
disease control fund in the district, the farmer said, adding that
cattle were the only source of power of the people in the area.
</P>
