recorded a substantial increase, thereby squeezing the net inflow
of foreign resources. The estimated foreign debt makes 39.4
percent of GDP and about 306 percent of the export earnings. Due
to the rescheduling of debt, service payments during 1999-2000 are
expected to decline by 8.5 percent to 1.4 billion dollars or 2.2
percent of GDP. (Pakistan-External Debts) 
