<HEADLINE> Pakistan Sets Export Target of 14 Bln U.S. Dollars for 2003 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Export Promotion
Bureau(EPB) has set an export target of 14 billion U.S. dollars to
be achieved by 2003, a local newspaper quoted EPB Chairman Tarique
Ikram as saying.
</P>
<P>
A six-point strategy, which is based on an evaluation of world
demand of goods and services, has been evolved for the new target.
This will help achieve the desired quantum jump in exports, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
Under the new strategy, the EPB will focus on increase in
exports in areas such as fisheries, software, fruit and vegetable,
engineering goods, auto parts, gems, diamonds, jewelry, marble,
granite and tourism, said the EPB chairman, adding that through
the new strategy, additional export target of 500 million U.S.
dollars would be achieved in less explored areas like China, South
America, Africa, Australia and Eastern Europe. 
