<HEADLINE> A Non-Malay Can Become Malaysia's Prime Minister: Mahathir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian prime minister
need not come from the Malays alone, non-Malay bumiputeras (
aboriginals) may also become the prime minister of Malaysia one
day when Malaysians of Chinese or Indian descent are accepted by
all the races, Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The process towards this end has started. Believe me, if we
are all sensitive to the tastes of Malaysians, the issue of race
and origin will no longer obstruct any Malaysian from holding any
post," he said when opening the 47th general assembly of the
Malaysian Chinese Association (MCA), the second largest political
party in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Cooperate in the political, economic and social fields and we
will all eradicate racialism and accept just any Malaysian to
become prime minister and fill any post," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Barisan Nasional (BN) (National Front) component parties,
including the MCA which is the largest Chinese-based party, should
work towards this end with the approach that is unique to Malaysia,
Mahathir, chairman of the ruling 14-party BN, said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysians are mainly composed of Malays, Chinese and Indians.
In the Malaysian history of its independence, the prime
ministership has always been held by Malays. 
</P>
