<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Children Conditions Improved among Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Juma said that following a nationwide vaccination campaign, the
death rate of 600 children below five years of age out of every
100,000 children born alive in 1978 was reduced to 42 last year.
However, he noted that the death rate of pregnant women was still
as high as 529 for every 100,000 children born alive due to
poverty and poor infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
He said children's enrollment for primary education has been
increased from 72 percent in 1993 to 82 percent last year but the
number of those who completed the education was still low.
</P>
