Women Affairs and Children Mwantunu Malale said that children were
the seedbank and needed good care to ensure they develop
profoundly to become future leaders and citizens.
</P>
<P>
Malale said urged parents and guardians to regard their
children not only as decorations of their families but rather as
human beings whose rights ought to be met.  The African
Children's Day is celebrated on June 16 every year across the
continent to commemorate the death of 15,000 children killed on
the same date in 1976 at Soweto town in South Africa when they
were protesting against the then apartheid regime.  
