</P>
<P>
New bombs were found only 14 sea miles offshore Venice, and
they were of the same type with those that exploded and injured
innocent Italian fishermen last year.
</P>
<P>
The fishermen also demanded the Italian government pay for
their losses due to the suspension of daily fishing activities
over safety concerns.
</P>
<P>
Alarm has been growing in the fishing sector over the impact of
last year's war in Kosovo. Reports said that some NATO pilots
dumped their bombs in the Adriatic on their way back to Italian
bases from missions in Yugoslavia. Several Venetian fishermen had
been injured when the bombs exploded in their fishing nets.
</P>
</TEXT>
