<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican Acupuncturists Meet to Exchange Experience </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Acupuncturists in Mexico held
a meeting Friday in Veracruz, some 400 kilometers east of Mexico
City, the first of its kind in the country to share experience in
acupuncture practice.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 acupuncturists from across the country attended the
meeting, which was inaugurated by Tomas Alcocer Gonzalez, chairman
of the National Union of Associations of Acupuncturists.
</P>
<P>
The chairman said that Mexican acupuncturists will analyze the
development of acupuncture in the country and will exchange
experiences in their practice.
</P>
<P>
He said that around 8,000 physicians practise acupuncture in
Mexico and that the union has 1,500 members.
</P>
<P>
Acupuncture is widely accepted by Mexicans as millions in the
country have been cured with the traditional Chinese way of
treating patients by special needles, the chairman said, adding
that many Mexican doctors have gone to China since 1981 to study
acupuncture and have gained satisfactory results after their
return to Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
