Saturday the death of 785 civilians during the first five months
of 2000, killed by guerrillas and rightist paramilitary, 170 over
the same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Armed Forces Command sources said that the Revolutionary Armed
Forces of Colombia (FARC) and of the National Liberation Army (ELN)
guerrillas killed 394 persons.
</P>
<P>
The rightist paramilitary United Self-Defenses of Colombia (AUC)
killed 391 persons of the total of people assassinated from
January to May in rural zones.
</P>
<P>
The report added that most of the victims were peasants whom
the paramilitary charge with being or supporting the insurgents.
</P>
<P>
Extreme left wing and right wing groups fight an irregular war
in most of the Colombian territory, while the government troops
try to impose order in the middle of the conflict.  
</P>
</TEXT>
